tag:blogger.com,1999:blog-6671019398434141469.post-75569130807498004452009-10-15T09:12:00.005+02:002010-11-26T11:15:13.174+01:00Groovy Goodness: Default Imports<p>Groovy allows to write dense code. For example we don't have to write explicit <code>import</code> statements for a lot of every day packages. The following packages are imported by default in Groovy:</p>
<pre class="brush:groovy;light:true">
java.io.* 
java.lang.* 
java.math.BigDecimal 
java.math.BigInteger 
java.net.* 
java.util.* 
groovy.lang.* 
groovy.util.* 
</pre>
<p>So we can write code like this without an import statement:</p>
<pre class="brush:groovy">
def now = new Date()
def file = new File(".")
def url = new URL('http://mrhaki.blogspot.com')
def list = new ArrayList()
</pre>Hubert Klein Ikkinkhttps://plus.google.com/116304108087638220732noreply@blogger.com0